\begin_layout Subsection
Derive a rate law
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So, what is the final value for 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\epsdice{6}}$
\end_inset

 we expect to observe? To ask this question, we can derive a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

rate law
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 that describes the reaction kinetics at play.
 
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Calculus (particularly differential equations) is intimidating for some
 students.
 Even if you can't do the steps below yourself, hopefully you can understand
 the steps we take in this derivation.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can start by writing out a differential equation: the change in the number
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsdice{6}$
\end_inset

 is given by how many appear at each time step, less the number that are
 lost.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dN_{six}}{dt}=\frac{N_{other\rightarrow\epsdice{6}}}{dt}-\text{\ensuremath{\frac{\ensuremath{N_{\epsdice{6}\rightarrow other}}}{dt}}}
\]

\end_inset

Substitute equations 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:rsix"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:runsix"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 above and simplify:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dN_{\epsdice{6}}}{dt}=\alpha\cdot\left(N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)\cdot p_{\epsdice{6}}-\alpha\cdot N_{\epsdice{6}}\cdot\left(1-p_{\epsdice{6}}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dN_{\epsdice{6}}}{dt}=\alpha\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-p_{\epsdice{6}}N_{\epsdice{6}}-N_{\epsdice{6}}+p_{\epsdice{6}}N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dN_{\epsdice{6}}}{dt}=\alpha\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)
\]

\end_inset

Rearrange so the 
\begin_inset Formula $dN_{\epsdice{6}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $dt$
\end_inset

 terms are on opposite sides of the equation:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dN_{\epsdice{6}}=\alpha\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)dt
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}}dN_{\epsdice{6}}=\alpha dt
\]

\end_inset

Integrate both sides:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int\frac{1}{p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}}dN_{\epsdice{6}}=\int\alpha dt
\]

\end_inset

Yielding:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)=\alpha t+C
\]

\end_inset

To figure out 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

, plug in values we know.
 In this case, we know that at 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

, we have some initial number of 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsdice{6}$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\epsdice{6},0}$
\end_inset

).
 (This is known as a boundary condition).
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}\right)=\text{\ensuremath{\alpha}\ensuremath{\cdot}}0+C
\]

\end_inset

Once we know 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

, do some algebra to solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\epsdice{6}}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)=\alpha t-ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}\right)+ln\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}\right)=\alpha t
\]

\end_inset

Use the rule 
\begin_inset Formula $log(a)-log(b)=log(a/b)$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-ln\left(\frac{p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}}{p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}}\right)=\alpha t
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{p_{\epsdice{6}ix}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}}{p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}}=e^{-\alpha t}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6}}=\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}\right)e^{-\alpha t}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{\epsdice{6}}=p_{\epsdice{6}}N-\left(p_{\epsdice{6}}N-N_{\epsdice{6},0}\right)e^{-\alpha t}
\]

\end_inset

Simplify:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N_{\epsdice{6}}=p_{\epsdice{6}}N-p_{\epsdice{6}}Ne^{-\alpha t}+N_{\epsdice{6},0}e^{-\alpha t}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
N_{\epsdice{6}}=p_{\epsdice{6}}N\left(1-e^{-\alpha t}\right)+N_{\epsdice{6},0}e^{-\alpha t}\label{eq:rate law}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

