 rates of the forward and reverse reaction, cause the two reactions to exactly
 offset one another.
 At 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{\epsdice{6}}=p_{\epsdice{6}}N$
\end_inset

, the rate of losing 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsdice{6}$
\end_inset

 is exactly offset by the rate of gaining 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsdice{6}$
\end_inset

 and the reaction has equilibrated.
 
\end_layout

