 energies of bonds formed in the products and reactants.
 Finally, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta S$
\end_inset

 (the change in entropy) might have been explained as a change in the amount
 of disorder between the products and reactants.
 Believe it or not, analogs of these exist even in something as simple as
 the DFR.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To show this, let's calculate the relative probability of being in the in
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $k=k_{2}$
\end_inset

