\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

measure of the disorder in a system.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 His equation was:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S_{shannon}=-\sum_{i}^{W}p_{i}log_{2}\left(p_{i}\right)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the probability of state 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 is the number of states, and 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is a constant.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this form, 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

